<title type="html"><![CDATA[Somebody teach me how to get GOOD sounds from FM synth]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6690&amp;p=64941#p64941"><![CDATA[
ADSR on the modulator allows the modulation depth (which creates the timbre) to change over time, much like pulse-width sweeps on a C64. Open SMB1.tfe and mute everything but the bass channel.<br /><br />I think <a href="http://the-all.org/tx81z/fm_overview.html" class="postlink">this</a> might as well be from the manual of a synth that used the same chip in the Genesis. A couple differences between the "pull-out reference card" nomenclature and TFM's are that A. operators 1 and 4 are swapped, B. algorithm numbers are off by one (e.g. TFM algo 4 is pull-out card algo 5), and C. the diagrams are rotated by 90 degrees.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Jul 26, 2010 8:56 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
