<title type="html"><![CDATA[Somebody teach me how to get GOOD sounds from FM synth]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6690&amp;p=64927#p64927"><![CDATA[
The tfmmaker distribution should come with some sample songs and sample instruments; try playing with those. Decent square and triangle patches are in my <a href="http://pics.pineight.com/nes/SMB1.tfe" class="postlink">SMB1.tfe</a> (<a href="http://pics.pineight.com/nes/SMB1.tfe.ogg" class="postlink">listen</a>).<br /><br />When you're starting out, you'll want to read up on <a href="http://www.sfu.ca/~truax/fmtut.html" class="postlink">FM synthesis theory</a> and use a 2-operator algorithm (#4). Note that when "MULT" is 0, it acts as if it's set to 1/2.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Jul 26, 2010 4:30 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
